    <note>Xu(3) Youzhi [15985] In Liu(2) Chang's funerary inscription for his son-in-law, Zhao(1) Kexiao(2) [15986] (q.v.), Youzhi is identified as the grandson of Xu(3) Hanlin, a Bingbu shangshu. Xu(3) Xuan [12236] was both a Hanlin xueshi and Bingbu shangshu under the Southern Tang (see Xuan's funerary inscription). I am assuming that Youzhi's father moved to Kaifeng with Xuan at beginning of Song.</note>
